machines.description: CNC machine tool specifications organized by enhancement level. CORE has foundational machine databases (lathe, 3D models, post-processor mapping). ENHANCED has per-manufacturer Level 4 databases with full kinematic chains, collision zones, transformation matrices. BY_COUNTRY indexes group manufacturers geographically. LEVEL5 is Haas-only with actual STEP CAD file references. ROOT files include kinematics engine, spec standards, and duplicate 3D model DB.

levels.CORE: Basic machine specs: travel, spindle, turret, coolant, rigidity. ~7 core databases covering lathe DBs, 3D model DBs (V2=68 machines, V3=108 machines), Okuma CAD, post-machine mapping.
levels.ENHANCED: Level 4 format: full kinematic chains, collision zones, transformation matrices, STEP file references, simulation-ready specs. 29 manufacturer-specific databases (Haas, DMG MORI, Mazak, Makino, Okuma, etc.) plus master index.
levels.LEVEL5: Haas-only Level 5: actual CAD STEP file paths for 61 machines. Highest fidelity with CAD mapping and new machines list.

materials.description: ISO-classified material properties with 127-parameter schema. Base material library organized by ISO cutting groups: P (steels), M (stainless), K (cast iron), N (nonferrous/aluminum/copper/titanium), S (superalloys). Each material has composition, physical/mechanical properties, Kienzle cutting forces, Johnson-Cook constitutive model, Taylor tool life, chip formation, friction/tribology, thermal machining, surface integrity, machinability indices, and recommended parameters. Files are split by alloy ranges (e.g., steels_151_200) and some have generated condition variants (hardness/heat-treatment matrices).

Also includes event bridging, database hub, kernel integration, and production integration modules. These are the glue between major subsystem categories.

infrastructure.description: Foundation infrastructure: validation, comparison, event bus, state management, and cross-module gateway routing. PRISM_VALIDATOR provides safe numerical operations with error codes. PRISM_COMPARE has float-safe comparison utilities. PRISM_GATEWAY routes cross-module API calls (material.get, tool.holder, toolpath.generate, etc.). PRISM_EVENT_BUS is pub/sub with wildcard support. PRISM_STATE_STORE is immutable state management.

overlap_analysis.generated_vs_base: Files ending in _generated contain condition variants of base materials; they supplement but do not replace base files
overlap_analysis.enhanced_vs_base: materials_enhanced files contain the SAME base materials as materials/ but with additional condition variants. Both should be loaded.
overlap_analysis.complete_vs_split: materials_complete monolithic files are merged versions of materials_enhanced. Use split files for lazy loading, complete for bulk access.

material_version_analysis.recommendation: For integration: (1) Use materials/ base files as canonical source for all ISO groups. (2) Supplement with materials_enhanced/ condition variants for P_STEELS and M_STAINLESS. (3) For S_SUPERALLOYS, prefer materials_v9_complete/ batches as most current. (4) Deprecate materials_complete/ monolithic files in favor of lazy-loaded split files. (5) Resolve aluminum overlap files. (6) Retire EXOTIC_MATERIALS_DATABASE.js, PRISM_MATERIALS_COMPLETE.js, PRISM_ENHANCED_MATERIAL_DATABASE.js as superseded.

levels.CORE: Level 1-3: Basic specs (travel, spindle, turret, coolant). Covers 7 databases, ~200 machines total across V2 and V3 3D model databases.
levels.ENHANCED: Level 4: Full kinematic chains, collision zones, transformation matrices, STEP references. 29 manufacturer-specific databases covering ~250+ machines from 29 manufacturers across 7 countries.
levels.LEVEL5: Level 5: Actual CAD STEP file paths. Haas-only (61 machines). Highest simulation fidelity.

duplicates_found.PRISM_MACHINE_3D_MODEL_DATABASE_V3: Exists both in CORE/ (2309 lines) and root machines/ (2295 lines). Likely extraction artifact - use CORE version.
duplicates_found.Haas_databases: Haas has V2 (1035 lines), V3 (1729 lines) at ENHANCED level, plus Level5 (967 lines) and HAAS_NEW_MACHINES (1020 lines). V3 supersedes V2 at ENHANCED level.

machine_hierarchy_analysis.recommendation: Load CORE databases first (universal machine specs), then ENHANCED per-manufacturer databases for detailed kinematics. LEVEL5 only needed for Haas simulation with actual CAD files. De-duplicate root-level V3 file.
